                                "byte_start": 108544,
                                "byte_stop": 142608,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion in Case Number 11-159, Astrue versus Capato."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.504,
                        "stop": 381.936,
                        "byte_start": 142608,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.504,
                                "stop": 19.916,
                                "byte_start": 142608,
                                "byte_stop": 188270,
                                "text": "This case concerns the entitlement of children conceived after the death of their father to Social Security survivor\u0027s benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.916,
                                "stop": 35.3,
                                "byte_start": 188270,
                                "byte_stop": 249814,
                                "text": "To qualify as a survivor of a deceased wage earner, a child so conceived, like child applicants generally, must be eligible to inherit from the insured under state intestacy law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.3,
                                "stop": 38.404,
                                "byte_start": 249814,
                                "byte_stop": 262248,
                                "text": "That standard was not met in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.404,
                                "stop": 49.712,
                                "byte_start": 262248,
                                "byte_stop": 307493,
                                "text": "The children in question are twins conceived through in vitro fertilization using deceased wage earner, Robert Capato\u0027s frozen sperm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.712,
                                "stop": 54.044,
                                "byte_start": 307493,
                                "byte_stop": 324733,
                                "text": "They were born 18 months after his death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.044,
                                "stop": 66.026,
                                "byte_start": 324733,
                                "byte_stop": 372694,
                                "text": "The Social Security Administration denied an application for benefits filed on the twins\u0027 behalf by their mother, Karen Capato, widow of the wage earner."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.026,
                                "stop": 82.285,
                                "byte_start": 372694,
                                "byte_stop": 437687,
                                "text": "The reason for the denial, Robert Capato died domiciled in Florida, and under that state law, children conceived after a parent\u0027s death do not qualify for intestate succession."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.285,
                                "stop": 92.288,
                                "byte_start": 437687,
                                "byte_stop": 477706,
                                "text": "On judicial review, the Federal District Court affirmed the denial of benefits, the Court of Appeals for the third Circuit however reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.288,
                                "stop": 103.288,
                                "byte_start": 477706,
                                "byte_stop": 521697,
                                "text": "It held that biological children of married parents are survivors entitled to benefits without regard to state intestacy law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.288,
                                "stop": 117.552,
                                "byte_start": 521697,
                                "byte_stop": 578853,
                                "text": "The governing Social Security provisions state first in 42 U.S.C. Section 402(d) that benefits are payable to every child as defined in Section 416(e)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.552,
                                "stop": 127.372,
                                "byte_start": 578853,
                                "byte_stop": 618036,
                                "text": "416(e) in turn defines child, as relevant here, to mean the child of an insured individual."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.372,
                                "stop": 151.829,
                                "byte_start": 618036,
                                "byte_stop": 715943,
                                "text": "A subsequent provision, Section 416(h)(2)(A), adds in determining whether an applicant is the child of an insured individual for purposes of this subchapter, the Commissioner of Social Security shall apply the intestacy law of the insured individual\u0027s domiciliary State."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.829,
                                "stop": 165.781,
                                "byte_start": 715943,
                                "byte_stop": 771741,
                                "text": "Respondent Karen Capato, in line with the Third Circuit, relies on the initial definition of child in 416(e), child means the child of an insured individual."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.781,
                                "stop": 177.024,
                                "byte_start": 771741,
                                "byte_stop": 816671,
                                "text": "Because the Capato twins are undeniably the children of Robert and Karen Capato, the Third Circuit reasoned they met before 416(e) definition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.024,
                                "stop": 203.36,
                                "byte_start": 816671,
                                "byte_stop": 921997,
                                "text": "There was no cause to refer to 416(h), the Court explained, for that Section is labeled determination of family status when, as in this case, claimants of the biological children of a married couple the Court said, there is no family status to determine so for 416(e) alone controls."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.36,
                                "stop": 214.698,
                                "byte_start": 921997,
                                "byte_stop": 967346,
                                "text": "But the Social Security Administration found that one must read on beyond 416(e) to determine who is a child for survivor\u0027s benefit purposes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.698,
                                "stop": 227.252,
                                "byte_start": 967346,
                                "byte_stop": 1017605,
                                "text": "Section 416(h) states explicitly that the definitions therein contained apply to the entire subchapter, including 416(e)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 227.252,
                                "stop": 247.496,
                                "byte_start": 1017605,
                                "byte_stop": 1098585,
                                "text": "In other words, the 416(e) tautological definition, \u0022child\u0022 means child is completed in 416(h) which instructs that the Capato twins could gain benefits only if they were entitled to inherit under the intestacy law of their father\u0027s domicile at death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 247.496,
                                "stop": 258.208,
                                "byte_start": 1098585,
                                "byte_stop": 1141426,
                                "text": "We agree that Section 416(h) serves as a gateway through which all applicants for benefits as a child must pass."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 258.208,
                                "stop": 272.811,
                                "byte_start": 1141426,
                                "byte_stop": 1199835,
                                "text": "Resort to state law on matters of family status is common in the Social Security Act, notably, the Act refers to state law to determine an applicant status as a wife, widow, husband or widower."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 272.811,
                                "stop": 288.04,
                                "byte_start": 1199835,
                                "byte_stop": 1260753,
                                "text": "The Act also sets several duration of relationship limitations and durational limits are also found in state statutes that accord inherit into rights to children conceived after their father\u0027s death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 288.04,
                                "stop": 301.142,
                                "byte_start": 1260753,
                                "byte_stop": 1313207,
                                "text": "In contrast, under the Court of Appeals\u0027 reading, biological children of married parents can gain benefits even if their father died many years before their birth."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 301.142,
                                "stop": 319.664,
                                "byte_start": 1313207,
                                "byte_stop": 1387290,
                                "text": "Reliance on state intestacy law to determine who is a child for survivor\u0027s benefit purposes, serves Congress\u0027 main aim to protect dependent members of wage earner\u0027s family against the hardship occasioned by the loss of the insured earning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 319.664,
                                "stop": 337.425,
                                "byte_start": 1387290,
                                "byte_stop": 1458343,
                                "text": "As this Court explained in prior case where state intestacy law provides that a child may take personal property from a father\u0027s estate, it may reasonably meet that what that the child were more likely be dependent during the parent\u0027s life and at his death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 337.425,
                                "stop": 371.868,
                                "byte_start": 1458343,
                                "byte_stop": 1596061,
                                "text": "In sum, we find the Social Security Administration\u0027s reading better attuned to the statute\u0027s text and its design to benefit primarily those that deceased wage earner actually supported in his or her lifetime and even if the agency\u0027s long standing interpretation is not the only reasonable one, it is at least a permissible construction entitled to deference under our decision in Chevron U.S.A. v. Natural Resources Defense Council."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 371.868,
                                "stop": 379.191,
                                "byte_start": 1596061,
                                "byte_stop": 1625318,
                                "text": "For the reasons stated spelled out in detail in the Court\u0027s opinion, we reverse the Third Circuit\u0027s judgement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 379.191,
                                "stop": 381.936,
                                "byte_start": 1625318,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
